  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "Q1 A mid-sized Indian pharmaceutical firm, 'Natco Pharma', has historically focused on a cost-focus generic drug strategy, targeting niche therapeutic segments with affordable products. As the industry consolidates and larger multinational firms enter these niches, Natco Pharma sees its market share declining. The management team is contemplating whether to stick with its cost-focus strategy or simultaneously pursue differentiation by introducing value-added features to its drugs (such as enhanced delivery mechanisms). They are wary of the risks of being 'stuck in the middle. Using Porter’s framework, how should Natco Pharma apply the principles of cost leadership and differentiation to avoid being stuck in the middle? What combination of strategies and operational changes would enable sustainable competitive advantage in a consolidating, competitive market?",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Q1 ",
        "formatting": {
          "bold": true
        },
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "A mid-sized Indian pharmaceutical firm, 'Natco Pharma', has historically focused on a cost-focus generic drug strategy, targeting niche therapeutic segments with affordable products. As the industry consolidates and larger multinational firms enter these niches, Natco Pharma sees its market share declining. The management team is contemplating whether to stick with its cost-focus strategy or simultaneously pursue differentiation by introducing value-added features to its drugs (such as enhanced delivery mechanisms). They are wary of the risks of being 'stuck in the middle. Using Porter’s framework, how should Natco Pharma apply the principles of cost leadership and differentiation to avoid being stuck in the middle? What combination of strategies and operational changes would enable sustainable competitive advantage in a consolidating, competitive market?",
        "formatting": {
          "bold": true
        },
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      }
    ],
    "metadata": {}
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "Answer:",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Answer:",
        "formatting": {
          "bold": true
        },
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      }
    ],
    "metadata": {}
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "Introduction",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Introduction",
        "formatting": {
          "bold": true
        },
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      }
    ],
    "metadata": {}
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "Today, the competitive environment for the Indian pharmaceutical industry, as defined by both domestic businesses and international corporations (MNCs), is increasing. The consequence of increased competition has been the necessity for companies to have a clear strategy that enables them to be successful in surviving and prospering over time. One example of a company that has successfully pursued a cost-focused strategy targeted towards providing lower-priced alternatives to high-cost branded drugs (generics) is Natco Pharma, which has historically capitalized on the generic pharmaceutical market by focusing on lesser-known, therapeutic segments of the market.",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Today, the competitive environment for the Indian pharmaceutical industry, as defined by both domestic businesses and international corporations (MNCs), is increasing. The consequence of increased competition has been the necessity for companies to have a clear strategy that enables them to be successful in surviving and prospering over time. One example of a company that has successfully pursued a cost-focused strategy targeted towards providing lower-priced alternatives to high-cost branded drugs (generics) is Natco Pharma, which has historically capitalized on the generic pharmaceutical market by focusing on lesser-known, therapeutic segments of the market.",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      }
    ],
    "metadata": {}
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "This has created an environment of increased competition for Natco Pharma and places it at risk of becoming “stuck in the middle,” as Michael Porter refers to being unable to demonstrate an overall leadership position in either cost or differentiation.",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "This has created an environment of increased competition for Natco Pharma and places it at risk of becoming “stuck in the middle,” as Michael Porter refers to being unable to demonstrate an overall leadership position in either cost or differentiation.",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      }
    ],
    "metadata": {}
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "Concepts and Strategic Application",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Concepts and Strategic Application",
        "formatting": {
          "bold": true
        },
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      }
    ],
    "metadata": {}
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "1. Avoiding the ‘Stuck in the Middle’ Situation",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "1. Avoiding the ‘Stuck in the Middle’ Situation",
        "formatting": {
          "bold": true
        },
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      }
    ],
    "metadata": {}
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "1. The Stuck in the Middle Problem Porter's model says that a firm cannot effectively do everything at once. A company must decide clearly whether it intends to be a low-cost leader or to differentiate itself in the market with value-added features. If a firm tries to offer both at the same time, it typically fails because the company does not have a sufficient plan for balancing the two strategies. ",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "1. The Stuck in the Middle Problem Porter's model says that a firm cannot effectively do everything at once. A company must decide clearly whether it intends to be a low-cost leader or to differentiate itself in the market with value-added features. If a firm tries to offer both at the same time, it typically fails because the company does not have a sufficient plan for balancing the two strategies. ",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      }
    ],
    "metadata": {}
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "In fact, if Natco raises the prices of the product(s) without putting any further added value to the product(s), customers will have alternatives to purchase from other, lower-priced suppliers. Thus, Natco must make a very definitive decision about where it wants to be. The better option is for Natco to stay with the current focus on niche customers and then make a definitive decision to compete based upon a cost basis or a differentiation basis. It is possible to use both strategies, but Natco must manage costs with a high degree of efficiency. ",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "In fact, if Natco raises the prices of the product(s) without putting any further added value to the product(s), customers will have alternatives to purchase from other, lower-priced suppliers. Thus, Natco must make a very definitive decision about where it wants to be. The better option is for Natco to stay with the current focus on niche customers and then make a definitive decision to compete based upon a cost basis or a differentiation basis. It is possible to use both strategies, but Natco must manage costs with a high degree of efficiency. ",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      }
    ],
    "metadata": {}
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "2. To Enhance Cost Leadership (By Maximizing Operational Productivity) ",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "2. To Enhance Cost Leadership (By Maximizing Operational Productivity) ",
        "formatting": {
          "bold": true
        },
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      }
    ],
    "metadata": {}
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "Assuming that Natco would like to remain focused on a cost leadership strategy and continue to pursue niche markets, the business cannot rely solely upon the current niche market approach; the firm must improve its operational productivity in order to achieve long-term success.",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Assuming that Natco would like to remain focused on a cost leadership strategy and continue to pursue niche markets, the business cannot rely solely upon the current niche market approach; the firm must improve its operational productivity in order to achieve long-term success.",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      }
    ],
    "metadata": {}
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "Process improvement is another important aspect for Natco to focus on going forward. By implementing better process technology such as continuous manufacturing, Natco will be able to lower its cost per output from previous years and increase its production rate at the same time. This will allow Natco to compete with much larger corporations as well.",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Process improvement is another important aspect for Natco to focus on going forward. By implementing better process technology such as continuous manufacturing, Natco will be able to lower its cost per output from previous years and increase its production rate at the same time. This will allow Natco to compete with much larger corporations as well.",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      }
    ],
    "metadata": {}
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "In addition, while Natco is currently in already existing niche markets, it can continue to grow and develop within these specific areas to increase economies of scale. By producing a larger volume in one of these segments, it will be able to decrease its costs and increase profitability.",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "In addition, while Natco is currently in already existing niche markets, it can continue to grow and develop within these specific areas to increase economies of scale. By producing a larger volume in one of these segments, it will be able to decrease its costs and increase profitability.",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      }
    ],
    "metadata": {}
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "Overall, by concentrating its efforts on efficiency and cost control, Natco’s position as a low-cost manufacturer will become more viable than ever before.",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Overall, by concentrating its efforts on efficiency and cost control, Natco’s position as a low-cost manufacturer will become more viable than ever before.",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      }
    ],
    "metadata": {}
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "3. Moving towards Focused Differentiation",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "3. Moving towards Focused Differentiation",
        "formatting": {
          "bold": true
        },
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      }
    ],
    "metadata": {}
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "Another area where Natco can create growth is to develop a focus on differentiated products by offering more value than just price competition with its competitors.",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Another area where Natco can create growth is to develop a focus on differentiated products by offering more value than just price competition with its competitors.",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      }
    ],
    "metadata": {}
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "In the case of Natco, there are ways to add value without completely reinventing their products. For example, they could improve aspects of already marketable product features such as the method of drug delivery, reduction of possible side effects, or comfort for patients.",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "In the case of Natco, there are ways to add value without completely reinventing their products. For example, they could improve aspects of already marketable product features such as the method of drug delivery, reduction of possible side effects, or comfort for patients.",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      }
    ],
    "metadata": {}
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "To be able to accomplish any of these changes in product value, however, Natco needs to alter the way it researches and develops new products. Presently, Natco exclusively manufactures generic versions of pharmaceuticals but can now research and develop products with additional features or “super generic” products.",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "To be able to accomplish any of these changes in product value, however, Natco needs to alter the way it researches and develops new products. Presently, Natco exclusively manufactures generic versions of pharmaceuticals but can now research and develop products with additional features or “super generic” products.",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      }
    ],
    "metadata": {}
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "At the same time, it is essential to develop a credible reputation with physicians and other health care providers. If a physician has confidence in the company's products, then that physician can charge reasonably higher prices for similar product offerings to cover any expenses incurred for added product value..",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "At the same time, it is essential to develop a credible reputation with physicians and other health care providers. If a physician has confidence in the company's products, then that physician can charge reasonably higher prices for similar product offerings to cover any expenses incurred for added product ",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "value.",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": ".",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      }
    ],
    "metadata": {}
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "4. Operational Changes Required",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "4. Operational Changes Required",
        "formatting": {
          "bold": true
        },
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      }
    ],
    "metadata": {}
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "Regardless of what strategy Natco chooses, some internal changes will need to take place:",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Regardless of what strategy Natco chooses, some internal changes will need to take place:",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      }
    ],
    "metadata": {}
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "An example would be with the supply chain; if they pursue a cost oriented strategy they will need to efficiently source and bulk purchase product. However, if they were to use a differentiation strategy, their supply chain would need to be flexible enough to fill special materials orders.",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "An example would be with the supply chain; if they pursue a ",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "cost oriented",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " strategy they will need to efficiently source and bulk purchase product. However, if they were to use a differentiation strategy, their supply chain would need to be flexible enough to fill special materials orders.",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      }
    ],
    "metadata": {}
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "As far as Marketing goes, the marketing focus will also change. Under a cost leadership strategy they should be marketing their products as affordable; while if they are pursuing a differentiation strategy quality and effectiveness will need to be the primary focus. Similarly, with R&D priorities they will also change from being efficiency based to being innovation based depending on what type of strategy is being implemented. So in summary, strategy is not just a theoretical decision made on a sheet of paper, it requires proper implementation across all disciplines.",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "As far as Marketing goes, the marketing focus will also change. Under a cost leadership ",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "strategy",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " they should be marketing their products as affordable; while if they are pursuing a differentiation strategy quality and effectiveness will need to be the primary focus. Similarly, with R&D priorities they will also change from being efficiency based to being innovation based depending on what type of strategy is being implemented. ",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "So",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " in summary, strategy is not just a theoretical decision made on a sheet of paper, it requires proper implementation across all disciplines.",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      }
    ],
    "metadata": {}
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "Conclusion",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Conclusion",
        "formatting": {
          "bold": true
        },
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      }
    ],
    "metadata": {}
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "To summarize, the current status of Natco Pharma is highly critical. Competition with MDs has increased and the cost strategy that once was the company's strength is starting to become weaker. The strategy that Natco Pharma is using going forward, may lead to being \"stuck in the middle\", which will negatively impact profitability. Although there are some areas of opportunity still available with respect to providing cost savings; the longer term strategic option of focused differentiation will provide greater relative value to Natco Pharma. ",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "To summarize, the current status of Natco Pharma is highly critical. Competition with MDs has increased and the cost strategy that once was the company's strength is starting to become weaker. The strategy that Natco Pharma is using going forward, may lead to being \"stuck in the middle\", which will negatively impact profitability.",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " ",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Although there are some areas of opportunity still available with respect to providing cost savings; the ",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "longer term",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " strategic option of focused differentiation will provide greater relative value to Natco Pharma",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": ".",
        "formatting": {},
