  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "1. Prioritization - Task Environment (Raw Material Prices)",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "1. Prioritization - Task Environment (Raw Material Prices)",
        "formatting": {
          "bold": true
        },
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      }
    ],
    "metadata": {}
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "While regulation and consumer pressure may appear to be the most serious issues being faced by GreenTech, the most pressing issue of concern to GreenTech is actually the rapid rise in supplier prices. Without an abatement of supplier costs, rising raw material prices will cause GreenTech to realize a loss in profit margins (and subsequently not only not having enough funds available to invest in new technologies and improvements) as a direct result of continued increases in supplier price.",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "While regulation and consumer pressure may appear to be the most serious issues being faced by GreenTech, the most pressing issue of concern to GreenTech is actually the rapid rise in supplier prices. Without an abatement of supplier costs, rising raw material prices will cause GreenTech to realize a loss in profit margins (and subsequently not only not having enough funds available to invest in new technologies and improvements) as a direct result of continued increases in supplier price.",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      }
    ],
    "metadata": {}
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "The business should seek alternate options for raw materials to address this matter. This may include research and development of alternative low-cost and/or easily obtainable inputs such as recycled or bio-based materials. In addition, the company can reduce their risk exposure to a single supplier by spreading their sourcing across multiple suppliers.",
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The business should seek alternate options for raw materials to address this matter. This may include research and development of alternative low-cost and/or easily obtainable inputs such as recycled or bio-based materials. In addition, the company can reduce their risk exposure to a single supplier by spreading their sourcing across multiple suppliers",
        "formatting": {},
        "metadata": {
          "style": "Normal"
        }
      },
      {
