    "type": "paragraph",
    "text": "When companies manage multiple suppliers, it is very challenging because they may not have the appropriate number of staff members available to manage the numerous suppliers effectively. Managing multiple suppliers requires dealing with multiple contracts, tracking multiple deliveries, and dealing with issues on a supplier-by-supplier basis (i.e., coordinating with suppliers to find solutions individually and within the schedule). This results in confusion and delays in completing work.",
